        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 6:45PM MDT until August 2 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles southwest
of Clayton, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Public reported.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of East Central Union County.

Thomas
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm has produced dangerous hail
and is capable of producing damaging winds.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
